# NovaLang Core Rules

## Project and platform scope

Work only inside `C:\Dev\NovaLang\novalang`.

NovaLang has three coordinated areas:

- React Web: `frontend/`
- Android Flutter: `mobile/novalang_flutter/`
- Shared source of truth: `shared/`

For a UI-only task, edit only the requested platform. Do not change `shared/`
or the other platform unless the task affects shared data or logic. Flutter is
Android-first, but Web and Flutter must remain aligned when they consume the
same shared source.

## 1. Đây là project đa nền tảng

Shared Data dùng chung cho:

- Flutter
- React Web

Nếu sửa business logic hoặc lesson data:

→ phải sửa Shared Source Of Truth.

Không fix riêng Flutter.

Không fix riêng Web.

Shared logic includes language catalogs and aliases, i18n, niches, levels,
exam tracks, lesson/curriculum data, vocabulary, grammar, kana/kanji,
exercise/checker logic, accepted answers, profile/onboarding, subscriptions,
and AI quota rules. Do not create a Flutter-only or Web-only copy that
conflicts with shared data.

---

## 2. Generated files

Không sửa:

- generated json
- generated assets

Luôn sửa:

Source
↓

Generate
↓

Sync

For shared configuration or i18n changes, update `shared/config/` or
`shared/i18n/`, then run `npm run sync:flutter-assets`. This mirrors data for
Flutter when needed. Do not hand-edit copied files under
`mobile/novalang_flutter/assets/shared/` unless explicitly instructed.

Future curriculum generation must update the approved source first, then
generate and sync; never repair generated output directly.

---

## 3. Localization

Không hard-code text.

UI phải dùng localization key.

UI language và Learning language là hai khái niệm khác nhau.

Every user-facing label, explanation, hint, feedback, and meaning option uses
the selected UI language. Learning-language target text remains in the learning
language. A Vietnamese UI must not contain English UI/options unless English is
the learning target.

Writing quality/register (how natural and how formal translated or
UI text sounds, across every language) follows
[`rules/content/naturalness-and-register.md`](../../rules/content/naturalness-and-register.md).
The default base register is `NATURAL_NEUTRAL_POLITE`; language-specific
details live only in `rules/languages/<languageCode>/style-and-register.md`.
Follow ADR-016 release-gate and QA semantics. A missing approved profile is
`LANGUAGE_STYLE_PROFILE_NOT_IMPLEMENTED`; do not translate literally at the
cost of natural native wording and do not auto-PASS content with heuristics.

---

## 4. Learning Languages

Format lesson dùng chung cho mọi learning language.

Không hard-code chỉ English hoặc Japanese.

Nội dung từng language sẽ được người dùng duyệt riêng.

Không được tự dịch.

---

## 5. Navigation

Back:

- Navigator.pop()

Giữ:

- scroll
- roadmap
- module
- unit

Không reset về đầu.

Preserve lesson session state needed to resume a learner, including lesson ID,
current step/index, completed state, completion time, and last visited time.

---

## 6. Audio

Basic Audio:

- dùng TTS hoặc audio cache

Không gọi AI Audio API cho fixed lesson.

Voice AI chỉ thuộc Pro.

---

## Responsive Flutter requirements

Flutter UI is mobile-first and uses `SafeArea`, `LayoutBuilder`, `MediaQuery`,
responsive spacing, full-width cards on small screens, and visible back
navigation. Do not design for one fixed phone size or use fixed page dimensions
such as `width: 390` or `height: 844`; small fixed icon sizes are acceptable.

---

## Lesson-format boundary

For an explicit `lessonFormat: five_cards` lesson,
`03_novalang_lesson_format_2_0.mdc` is the Single Source of Truth. Do not apply
legacy exercise counts, access allocations, exercise maps, or validation rules
to it. Such rules belong only to the non-opt-in legacy scope in
`02_novalang_lesson_standard.mdc`.

---

## 7. Validation

Nếu task liên quan curriculum:

Phải chạy:

- Generate
- Validate
- Smoke
- Flutter Analyze
- Flutter Test

Không được báo PASS nếu chưa chạy.

Before editing, verify the current workspace with `pwd`,
`git rev-parse --show-toplevel`, and `git status --short`.

For Flutter work, run `flutter pub get` and `flutter analyze`; run
`flutter build apk --debug` when required by the task. For Web work, run
`npm run build` when required. Report any missing SDK or configuration issue.

After each task, report the working directory, task type, changed Web/Flutter/
shared files, sync status, requested checks, and whether a commit was made.
